frus:attachment.head:
The Chairman of the American Delegation (
    Davis
) to President Roosevelt

Memorandum by the Chairman of the American Delegation
    (Davis)Of a
    conversation held at the Foreign Office, London, September 6, 1933.
    Present were Sir John Simon, Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs;
    Alexander Montagu George Cadogan, Adviser on League of Nations Affairs;
    Mr. Davis; and Hugh Wilson, American delegate.
